{"id": "duc04-testb-31:9#29", "contents": "The pressure to form a secular coalition is mounting, as Turkey's secular parties seek to prevent the Islamic Virtue Party from gaining power. As the largest party in Parliament, Virtue is well-positioned to take the reins, but the powerful military is strongly opposed to an Islamic-led government. Ecevit is expected to meet with Yilmaz and other party leaders in the coming days to discuss the possibility of a coalition, with the goal of forming a stable and secular government."}
